import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other Injuries')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of wounds, other injuries, and diseases over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wounds'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean : {data['wounds'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median : {data['wounds'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

    data['other'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)

    plt.axvline(data['other'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')

    plt.axvline(data['disease'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['wounds'], data['other'])
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the number of wounds and other injuries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of wounds')
    plt.ylabel('Number of other injuries')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
